"{\"uid\": \"theconversation.com-anatomy-of-a-wave-what-makes-the-olympic-surf-break-at-teahupoo-unique-and-so-challenging-235301\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Honorary Senior Lecturer, Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, University of Auckland, Waipapa Taumata Rau  Tom Shand is affiliated with the Engineering Consultancy Tonkin + Taylor and with the industry association PIANC (World Association for Waterborne Transport Infrastructure).\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 117, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rau\", \"score\": 0.9999986523644097, \"rank\": 1.3475232457102608e-06, \"text\": \"Rau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rau\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"University of Auckland, Waipapa Taumata Rauprovides funding as a member of The Conversation NZ.\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"University of Aucklandprovides funding as a member of The Conversation AU.\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners  https://doi.org/10.64628/AA.htsmagjpn  Share article  Print article  As the Olympics get going in earnest this week, not everyone's attention is focused on host city Paris.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 657, \"end\": 662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999175363313, \"rank\": 8.246373771466946e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surf fans are heading to Tahiti, half a world away in French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 689, \"end\": 695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9973419008078123, \"rank\": 0.002665183514556378, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 725, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9868006006778147, \"rank\": 0.013375953878807117, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why?\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, apart from the French coast resembling a lake at this time of year, on the south-west coast of Tahiti Iti is a wave unlike any other on the planet: Teahupo'o, which translates somewhat ominously as \\\"place of skulls\\\".\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 763, \"end\": 769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9979045731594878, \"rank\": 0.0020098075186687605, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave is unique in the way it breaks.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 1006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The lower part of the wave appears to drop away below sea level, with the top half folding over dramatically to create an almost cartoonishly perfect form.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is both the weight of water in the plunging lip and the risk of injury or death for a surfer in the wrong position that make this one of the world's heaviest waves (in both senses of the word).\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To understand why the wave breaks like this, we need to start withbathymetry: the shape of the seabed that influences waves as they approach the shore.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At Teahupo'o, acombination of factorscomes into play.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves arriving at Teahupo'o generally originate from intense \\\"roaring forties\\\" storm systems south of New Zealand.\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8282313449332459, \"rank\": 0.1420817944772724, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the waves reach Tahiti they have become ordered swell, with wave heights of two to five metres and periods of 14 to 20 seconds between successive waves.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9973419008078123, \"rank\": 0.002665183514556378, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These types of long-period waves normally start interacting with the seabed at depths of around 200 metres.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On most coasts, this depth would occur up to several kilometres offshore.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 2031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But at Teahupo'o, it is much closer, just a couple of hundred metres.\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This rapid change in depth forces the wave to \\\"shoal\\\" very quickly - the wave speed slows, the distance between waves compresses and the wave height increases.\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The change is so abrupt that the wave is still very linear - it has not had time to develop the peaked crest and flat trough (the lowest part of the wave) typical of waves in shallow water.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves breaking on this type of steep slope would typically collapse, breaking from the middle of the wave and creating an unsurfable mess.\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this does not happen.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At around ten metres' depth, a flatter shelf in the reef allows the wave to stabilise and \\\"stand up\\\" with a steep front face, before finally breaking as the reef rises again.\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And break it does.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to the linearity, there is far more water in the crest (the part above water) then most waves, and a deeper trough in front.\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2946, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes for the characteristic below-sea-level break at Teahupo'o, with the overturning lip being half the wave height, and a jet of compressed air forced out of the wave's barrel after breaking.\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The larger the wave, the closer to the steep offshore ramp it breaks, and the more extreme the plunging.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A range of other unique features contribute to the way the wave breaks at Teahupo'o - and what makes it so challenging as a surfing wave.\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A deep channel runs alongside the shallow reef shelf.\", \"from\": 3393, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave does not break in this deeper area, allowing it to peel - to break in one direction (in this case towards the left looking towards the shore) - and enabling surfers to ride the wave before it finally closes out onto shallow reef.\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A part of the shallow reef platform extends offshore, into the reef pass.\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This shallow area bends and focuses wave energy from the wider, deeper part of the wave back into the breaking wave.\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This happens particularly on more westerly orientated swells, increasing the intensity of breaking.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 3977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as this, the Teahupo'o wave breaks in a direction nearly opposite to the prevailing trade winds, keeping the wave face smooth.\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 4113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A low tidal range also limits the times the reef is too deep or too shallow to surf.\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the wave is near the Passa Hava'e reef pass, which helps the wave's focusing and breaking.\", \"from\": 4200, \"to\": 4294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4225, \"end\": 4230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"score\": 0.9999999954807208, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Passa\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But because it is not right in the pass, the wave is not affected by high tidal or wave-induced currents.\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New-generation wave models that simulate individual waves, rather than just average energy density, provide insight into what creates a surf break such as Teahupo'o (see figure below).\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These models provide insight into what happens as waves shoal and refract (bend and focus) over the seabed as they approach break point.\", \"from\": 4587, \"to\": 4723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They also significantly improve our understanding of what makes a particular surf break unique.\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This can help in assessing the potential impact of human or natural modifications to the environment.\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 4922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2025,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 4924, \"to\": 4978, \"entities\": []}]}"